14 WHEREAS, these organizations are committed to fostering a thriving environment for small
15 businesses and entrepreneurship in Georgia.
16 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE that the members of this body
17 commend the Small Business Majority, the Women's Entrepreneurial Opportunity Project
18 Inc., the Urban League of Greater Atlanta, the Russell Innovation Center for Entrepreneurs,
19 Our Village United, Kindred Futures, and Georgia First for their efforts to empower
20 entrepreneurs, promote economic development, and advance opportunities for small business
21 owners across the State of Georgia.
22 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the members of this body recognize March 5, 2025, as
23 Small Business Advocacy Day in acknowledgment of the many remarkable contributions
24 made to Georgia's economy by small businesses.
25 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Secretary of the Senate is authorized and directed
26 to make appropriate copies of this resolution available for distribution to the public and the
27 press.
